OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FCovid: Postponing          
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25FManchester Pride cost      
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fcharity #2.5m in revenue   
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The charity that organises Manchester  
OL,6, Pride saw its income drop by #2.5m in  
OL,7, 2020 after the festival was moved      
OL,8, entirely online due to Covid-19.       
OL,10,FThe organisation's accounts showed an  
OL,11,F85% dip in revenue, largely due to the 
OL,12,Fpostponement of the in-person event.   
OL,14,FDonations also dropped from #114,000 in
OL,15,F2019 to #9,000 in 2020.                
OL,17,FThe chairman of Manchester Pride's     
OL,18,Fboard of trustees said "some difficult 
OL,19,Fbut necessary choices" had been made,  
OL,20,Fincluding three redundancies.          
